body:
# Notion Pages

Pages are the fundamental content unit in Notion. Every page lives under a parent (either another page or a database) and contains properties and content blocks. The Pages API lets agents create, read, update, and archive pages programmatically.

## Create

To create a page, POST to `/v1/pages` with a `parent` (page ID or database ID), `properties` (at minimum a title), and optional `children` (block content).

```javascript
const { Client } = require('@notionhq/client');
const notion = new Client({ auth: process.env.NOTION_TOKEN });

const page = await notion.pages.create({
  parent: { database_id: parentId },
  properties: {
    Name: {
      title: [{ text: { content: 'My New Page' } }]
    },
    Status: {
      select: { name: 'In Progress' }
    }
  },
  children: [
    {
      object: 'block',
      type: 'paragraph',
      paragraph: {
        rich_text: [{ text: { content: 'Page content goes here.' } }]
      }
    }
  ]
});
```

## Read and Update

Retrieve a page with `notion.pages.retrieve({ page_id })`. Update properties with `notion.pages.update({ page_id, properties })`. To update content blocks, use the Blocks API (see [[notion/blocks#append-children]]).

```javascript
// Retrieve
const existing = await notion.pages.retrieve({ page_id: pageId });

// Update properties
const updated = await notion.pages.update({
  page_id: pageId,
  properties: {
    Status: { select: { name: 'Done' } }
  }
});
```

## Properties

Page properties depend on the parent database schema. Common property types:

| Type | API Format | Example |
|------|-----------|----------|
| Title | `title: [{ text: { content } }]` | Page name |
| Rich text | `rich_text: [{ text: { content } }]` | Description field |
| Number | `number: 42` | Priority score |
| Select | `select: { name: 'Option' }` | Status dropdown |
| Multi-select | `multi_select: [{ name: 'Tag' }]` | Labels |
| Date | `date: { start: '2026-04-10' }` | Due date |
| Checkbox | `checkbox: true` | Completion flag |
| URL | `url: 'https://...'` | Link field |
| Relation | `relation: [{ id: 'page-id' }]` | Cross-database link |

## Content Blocks

Page content is composed of blocks appended as children. Blocks include paragraphs, headings, lists, toggles, callouts, code, images, and embeds. See [[notion/blocks]] for the full block type reference and [[notion/blocks#rich-text]] for text formatting.

## Archive

Archive a page by setting `archived: true` in an update call. This is a soft delete — the page moves to trash and can be restored.

```javascript
await notion.pages.update({
  page_id: pageId,
  archived: true
});
```
